description.narrative:
UNICEF supported the country in the generation of evidence for decision-making about children´s rights. To that end, it supported the development the MICS Household Survey 2019 and three studies started in 2018 were completed: 
1) Situation of Children on the Move; 
2) Institutionalized Children in the Protection System; 
3) The KAP study about Child Marriage and Early Unions. A review about the progress of children´s rights after 30 years of the CRC was produced. The Management Response Plans of the three evaluations carried out in 2017-2018 were implemented. 
The initiatives on prevention of sexual exploitation and CMEU were evaluated.
 | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/02/2020
